  <Docs>
    <summary>Alignments specify where a view should be placed within a cell group and
 what size it should be.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">Alignments specify where a view should be placed within a cell group and
 what size it should be.
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
 The <c><see cref="T:Android.Widget.GridLayout+LayoutParams" /></c> class contains a <c><see cref="P:Android.Widget.GridLayout.LayoutParams.RowSpec" /></c>
 and a <c><see cref="P:Android.Widget.GridLayout.LayoutParams.ColumnSpec" /></c> each of which contains an
 <c>alignment</c>. Overall placement of the view in the cell
 group is specified by the two alignments which act along each axis independently.
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
  The GridLayout class defines the most common alignments used in general layout:
 <c><see cref="!:Android.Widget.GridLayout.TOP" /></c>, <c><see cref="!:Android.Widget.GridLayout.LEFT" /></c>, <c><see cref="!:Android.Widget.GridLayout.BOTTOM" /></c>, <c><see cref="!:Android.Widget.GridLayout.RIGHT" /></c>, <c><see cref="P:Android.Widget.GridLayout.Start" /></c>,
 <c><see cref="P:Android.Widget.GridLayout.End" /></c>, <c><see cref="P:Android.Widget.GridLayout.Center" /></c>, <c><see cref="!:Android.Widget.GridLayout.BASELINE" /></c> and <c><see cref="P:Android.Widget.GridLayout.Fill" /></c>.
</para>
